id: pm-83rt
title: Fix Windows nightly full-test path and permission assumptions
description: "GitHub Nightly Validation run 27898852339 failed on windows-latest Node 20 after the 2026.6.21 release. Failures are cross-platform test assumptions around POSIX path substrings, chmod/read-only behavior, and Windows temp cleanup semantics in eval, search-cache, telemetry-runtime, and extension-command tests. Reuse closed Windows-nightly lineage rather than reopening stale shipped items."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: ci,nightly,tests,windows
created_at: "2026-06-21T08:57:26.311Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-21T10:05:21.870Z"
author: codex-gpt5
parent: pm-u9d0
environment: GitHub Actions windows-latest Node 20
repro_steps: "Run Nightly Validation on main or inspect gh run 27898852339; windows-latest Node 20 pnpm test fails in eval-command, extension-command, search-cache, and telemetry-runtime specs."
resolution: "Fixed Windows/nightly and post-merge CI test reliability by making path assertions separator-neutral, guarding chmod-only permission-denial branches to POSIX, retrying telemetry OTLP temp cleanup while detached workers finish, and allowing the MCP error-path integration test enough time under full-suite coverage."
expected_result: Nightly Validation full test matrix passes on Windows without POSIX-only assertions or chmod-only permission assumptions.
actual_result: Focused linked pm tests passed in the schema sandbox; direct repo coverage passed literal 100/100/100/100 across 241 files and 4796 tests; manual temp-dir smoke passed with isolated tracker/global paths.
component: CI test suite
